# DOCX Generation Conventions

These rules apply to **every** Word document generated with `python-docx` in this workspace.

## Page Setup

- **Page size:** US Letter (8.5" × 11")
- **All margins:** 0.75" (left, right, top, bottom)

## Color Palette

| Token | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|-------|
| Primary | `#1F4E79` | Titles, headings, footer brand, default table headers, horizontal rules |
| Secondary | `#2E75B6` | Secondary table headers (sub-tables, detail tables) |
| Muted text | `#64748B` | Header text, page numbers |
| Light accent | `#94A3B8` | Header/footer border lines, confidentiality notice |
| Row stripe | `#E8F0FE` | Alternating table row background (odd data rows) |
| White | `#FFFFFF` | Table header row text |

## Title Page

Every document starts with a dedicated title page (no header displayed on this page):

1. **6 blank paragraphs** for vertical spacing
2. **Document title:** centered, bold, 28pt, color `#1F4E79`
3. **Subtitle:** centered, 16pt, color `#64748B`
4. **Blank paragraph**
5. **Horizontal rule:** centered, "━" × 60, 10pt, color `#1F4E79`
6. **Blank paragraph**
7. **Metadata fields** — centered, label bold 10pt `#1F4E79`, value 10pt, 2pt space after / 0pt before each field. Include fields appropriate to the document (e.g., version, date, author, classification).
8. **Page break** after title page

## Header

- Set `different_first_page_header_footer = True` so the title page has no header
- **Left:** Date string, 8pt, color `#64748B`
- **Right (tab stop at 7.0"):** Document title + version, 8pt, color `#64748B`
- **Bottom border:** single line, weight 4, space 1, color `#94A3B8`

## Footer

Applied to **all pages** including the title page:

- **Left:** "Astraios", 8pt, **bold**, color `#1F4E79`
- **Center (tab stop at 3.5"):** "Proprietary & Confidential", 8pt, *italic*, color `#94A3B8`
- **Right (tab stop at 7.0"):** "Page " + `PAGE` field code, 8pt, color `#64748B`
- **Top border:** single line, weight 4, space 1, color `#94A3B8`

Use Word field codes (`w:fldChar` begin/end with `instrText " PAGE "`) for page numbers.

## Table Formatting

- **Style:** "Table Grid", center-aligned (`WD_TABLE_ALIGNMENT.CENTER`)
- **Header row:** white text (`#FFFFFF`), bold, 8pt, background `#1F4E79` (or `#2E75B6` for secondary/detail tables)
- **Data rows:** 7.5pt font
- **Alternating row shading:** odd data rows (1-indexed) get `#E8F0FE` background via `w:shd` element
- **Cell shading helper:** set `w:fill` and `w:val="clear"` on `tcPr > w:shd`

## Typography

| Element | Font Size | Weight / Style |
|---------|-----------|----------------|
| Document title | 28pt | Bold |
| Subtitle | 16pt | Normal |
| Heading 1 | default | — |
| Heading 2 | default | — |
| Heading 3 | default | — |
| Body text / prose | 9pt | Normal |
| Metadata field labels | 9–10pt | Bold |
| Metadata field values | 9–10pt | Normal |
| Bullet lists ("List Bullet") | 9pt | Normal; nested indent 1.27 cm |
| Numbered lists ("List Number") | 9pt | Normal; restart numbering per sequence |
| Code blocks | 7pt | Courier New |
| Code block spacing | — | 4pt before, 4pt after |
| TM impact text | 8pt | Normal |

## Section Break Headings (e.g., Appendices)

For major section breaks that should NOT use auto-numbered chapter headings:

- Centered, `page_break_before = True`
- 36pt space before, 24pt space after
- Bold, 22pt, color `#1F4E79`
- Followed by horizontal rule: "━" × 80, 8pt, color `#1F4E79`, 12pt space after

## Markdown-to-DOCX Heading Mapping

When converting markdown content into a DOCX:

| Markdown | DOCX Level | Context |
|----------|------------|---------|
| `#` | Heading 1 | Top-level sections (or Heading 3 inside appendices) |
| `##` | Heading 2 | Subsections (or Heading 3 inside appendices) |
| `###` | Heading 3 | Individual entries (or Heading 4 inside appendices) |
| `####` | Heading 4 / 5 | Sub-sections within entries |

## Inline Markdown Rendering

- `**bold text**` → bold run at current paragraph font size
- `- bullet` → "List Bullet" style; `  - nested` → indent 1.27 cm
- `1. item` → "List Number" style; restart numbering when a non-numbered element intervenes
- `` ``` `` code blocks → Courier New 7pt paragraph
- Pipe tables → Word tables using the table formatting rules above
- `---` horizontal rules → skip (used as visual separators in markdown, not rendered)

## Enum Value Display

When showing enumeration values in tables, display up to 6 entries in `key=value` format separated by semicolons. If more exist, append `(+N more)`.
